Basecamp
========

Basecamp service hook allows you to post comments into the project's message thread. No single message threads per commit are being created.

Install Notes
-------------

  1. subdomain should be your Basecamp subdomain
  2. api token should be a valid API token you obtained from basecamp settings, and links to user account
  4. project should be the IDof the project that you want to post into (not the name)
  5. post should be the ID of the message that you want to post the comment using (not the name)
  6. ssl should be enabled for accounts that need SSL.


Configuration
-------------

    basecamp:
      subdomain: foo (if your url is foo.basecamphq.com)
      ssl: true/false
      api_token: TOKEN
      project: PROJECT_ID
      post: POST_ID